  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000327">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A pneumatic actuator is an actuator that operates using pneumatic power.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um atuador pneumático é um atuador que opera usando energia pneumática.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every pneumatic actuator is an actuator that has operating medium some pneumatic power.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] An actuator that is intended to be operated by pneumatic power.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;PNEUMATIC ACTUATOR&gt; is an &lt;INSTRUMENTATION ITEM&gt; and a &lt;CONTROLLED ACTUATOR&gt; that is intended to be operated by pneumatic power</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] An actuator that is intended to be operated by pneumatic power.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type where pneumatic mechanism is necessary but may not be sufficient under OWA. Specialized pneumatic equipment (pneumatic tools, pneumatic cylinders) might have pneumatic power but should not be classified as actuators without additional validation of their actuation role in control systems.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2502"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2504"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2501"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2503"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000207"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pneumatic actuator</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">atuador pneumático</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(PneumaticActuator(x) → Actuator(x) ∧ ∃y(PneumaticPower(y) ∧ hasOperatingMedium(x,y)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b3015">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FluidPortion"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasInput"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000266">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A filter cartridge is a filter that has a replaceable filter medium in a cartridge form factor designed for insertion into and removal from a filter housing.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um cartucho de filtro é um filtro que possui um meio filtrante substituível em formato de cartucho projetado para inserção e remoção de um alojamento de filtro.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1304"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1303"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1302"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000081"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">filter cartridge</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">cartucho de filtro</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A filter element intended to collect particles from a stream in a filter or strainer.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A filter element intended to collect particles from a stream in a filter or strainer.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FILTER CARTRIDGE&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;FILTER ELEMENT&gt; intended to collect particles from a stream in a filter or strainer</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (FilterCartridge(x) → Filter(x) ∧ ∃m (ReplaceableFilterMedium(m) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,m)) ∧ ∃p (CartridgeGeometryProperty(p) ∧ bearerOf(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every filter cartridge is a filter that has a replaceable filter medium as component part and bears a cartridge geometry property.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type where the structural differentia (cartridge geometry and replaceability) is necessary but making it sufficient under OWA could lead to false positives - other equipment containing replaceable filter elements might be incorrectly classified as filter cartridges rather than their proper specialized categories.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
