  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000353">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">atuador solenoide</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">solenoid actuator</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every solenoid actuator is an electric actuator that has a solenoid as component part and has a plunger as component part and converts electrical power to linear mechanical motion.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b3012"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000260"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000207"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(SolenoidActuator(x) → ElectricActuator(x) ∧ ∃s(Solenoid(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s)) ∧ ∃p(Plunger(p) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SOLENOID ACTUATOR&gt; is an &lt;ELECTRIC ACTUATOR&gt; and an &lt;ELECTRIC TO MECHANICAL ENERGY CONVERTER&gt; and an &lt;ELECTROMECHANICAL DEVICE&gt;  that is utilizing a continuous duty linear solenoid to convert electrical energy into mechanical power via a plunger with an axial stroke in either a push or pull action</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um atuador solenoide é um atuador elétrico que utiliza um solenoide linear de serviço contínuo para converter energia elétrica em energia mecânica através de um êmbolo com curso axial em ação de empurrar ou puxar.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A solenoid actuator is an electric actuator that utilizes a continuous duty linear solenoid to convert electrical energy into mechanical power via a plunger with an axial stroke in either a push or pull action.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type defined by solenoid mechanism. Under OWA, sufficient conditions would force any device with solenoid and plunger components to be classified as a solenoid actuator, potentially misclassifying complex hybrid devices or specialized equipment containing solenoid components but serving different primary functions.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1207">
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ElectricalConnectionProcess"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2918">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasSpecifiedOutput"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/MaterialPortion"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b3047">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/StatorWinding"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtSomeTime"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000373">
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type based on structural configuration. Under OWA, asserting sufficient conditions for vessel head closure would inappropriately classify any part that closes a vessel (including specialized manifolds, complex multi-port heads, or custom closures) as standard vessel heads, potentially creating false positives in maintenance categorization.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">vessel head</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">tampo de vaso</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b3413"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every vessel head is a fiat object part that is part of some vessel and realizes a vessel closure role.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma FiatObjectPart que é parte de um vaso e que fecha o casco do vaso fornecendo uma fronteira terminal para contenção.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A FiatObjectPart that is part of a vessel and that closes a vessel shell by providing an end boundary for containment.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;VESSEL HEAD&gt; is an &lt;EQUIPMENT COMPONENT&gt; that is intended to close a vessel shell.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(VesselHead(x) → FiatObjectPart(x) ∧ ∃y(Vessel(y) ∧ partOf(x,y)) ∧ ∃r(VesselClosureRole(r) ∧ realizes(x,r)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
