  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000368">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;UPS UNIT&gt; is an &lt;AC ELECTRIC POWER SUPPLY UNIT&gt; that maintains a uninterrupted supply of electric power to the equipment it protects</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] An A.C. power supply unit that maintains a continuous supply of electric power to the equipment it protects.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] An ac power supply unit that maintains a continuous supply of electric power to the equipment it protects.</skos:definition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b3328"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every UPS unit is electrical equipment that has the function of maintaining uninterrupted AC electric power supply.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma unidade UPS é um equipamento elétrico que possui a função projetada de manter o fornecimento ininterrupto de energia elétrica AC para equipamentos protegidos durante distúrbios de energia.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A UPS unit is electrical equipment that bears the designed function of maintaining uninterrupted AC electric power supply to protected equipment during power disturbances.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">ups unit</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">unidade UPS</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(UPSUnit(x) ↔ ElectricalEquipment(x) ∧ ∃f(UninterruptedPowerSupplyFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000329">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um MaterialArtifact que possui uma InterfacingFunction e que é capaz de fornecer um ponto de interface para comunicação com outro objeto.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A MaterialArtifact that bears an InterfacingFunction and that is capable of providing a point of interface for communication with another object.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">port</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">MaterialArtifact que possui uma InterfacingFunction e</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Port(x) ↔ (MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃f(InterfacingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2533"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Port ≡ MaterialArtifact ⊓ ∃bearerOf.InterfacingFunction</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;PORT&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that is capable of &lt;PROVIDING&gt; a point of interface for communication with another object</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000222">
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive classification based on structural configuration. Under OWA, sufficient conditions for enclosure structure could lead to over-classification of complex assemblies that contain enclosure elements but serve different primary functions (e.g., pressure vessels, housings, containers).</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000222"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Casing(x) → Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(EnclosureFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃w(CasingWall(w) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,w)) ∧ ∃p(PressureContainmentFunction(p) ∧ hasFunction(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CASING&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and an &lt;ENCLOSURE&gt; that is the stationary enclosure of a machine intended to contain a fluid and equipment internals</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] An enclosure that can maintain a pressure difference.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] Large-diameter pipe lowered into an openhole and cemented in place.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] One of several strings of steel pipe in a well design that, together with cement, forms a barrier to fluid movement along the drilled hole. It is commonly at least partly cemented in the wellbore.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every casing is an assembly that has an enclosure function and has component part some casing wall and has function some pressure containment function.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b406"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b405"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b404"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A casing is an assembly that provides structural enclosure with pressure containment capability, characterized by walls that separate internal components or fluids from the external environment.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um casing é um conjunto que fornece invólucro estrutural com capacidade de contenção de pressão, caracterizado por paredes que separam componentes internos ou fluidos do ambiente externo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">casing</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">casing</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2840">
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2841"/>
    <rdf:first rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000296">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A hose is a flexible pipe designed to conduct liquids under pressure while accommodating positional movement and bending.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma mangueira é um tubo flexível projetado para conduzir líquidos sob pressão enquanto acomoda movimento posicional e flexão.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every hose is a pipe that has flexibility and is capable of conducting liquids under pressure.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;HOSE&gt; is a &lt;TUBULAR&gt; that is flexible and capable of conducting liquids under pressure</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A tubular which is flexible and capable of conveying liquids under pressure.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A tubular which is flexible and capable of conveying liquids under pressure.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1857"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000321"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1855"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1856"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1858"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions because this is a constructive type defined by physical properties (flexibility). Under OWA, asserting equivalence would force any artifact with flexibility and pressure capability to be classified as a hose, potentially including complex equipment with flexible components that should not be categorized as standard hoses.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">mangueira</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">hose</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Hose(x) → Pipe(x) ∧ ∃q(Flexibility(q) ∧ hasQuality(x,q)) ∧ ∃c(PressurizedFluidConduction(c) ∧ capableOf(x,c)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1200">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ElectricalConductionProcess"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
