  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000366">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">turbine</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">turbina</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma turbina é um conjunto que possui uma função de extração de energia e tem eixo rotativo e pás de interação com fluidos que extraem energia de fluidos em movimento e a convertem em trabalho mecânico útil.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A turbine is an assembly that bears an energy extraction function and has rotating shaft and fluid-interacting blades that extract energy from flowing fluids and convert it into useful mechanical work.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that is intended to rotate within a fluid and to transform energy within a fluid into mechanical power.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[DEXPI] An object that is a rotary mechanical device that extracts energy from a fluid flow and converts it into useful work (from ``_).</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;TURBINE&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;DRIVER(function)&gt; that is a rotary mechanical device that extracts energy from a fluid flow and converts it into useful work</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Turbine(x) ↔ Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(EnergyExtractionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃s(RotatingShaft(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s)) ∧ ∃b(FluidInteractionBlades(b) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,b)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b3289"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every turbine is an assembly that bears an energy extraction function and has component parts including a rotating shaft, fluid interaction blades, casing, and bearing system.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2425">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/CurvedFluidPassage"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000291">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (GlobeValveBody(x) → ValveBody(x) ∧ ∃g (GlobularGeometry(g) ∧ hasDesignCharacteristic(x,g)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;GLOBE VALVE BODY&gt; is a &lt;VALVE BODY&gt; of a globe valve</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type defined by structural geometry. Under OWA, asserting equivalence based on globular geometry alone could lead to false classifications of complex assemblies or hybrid components that contain globular elements but should not be classified as standard globe valve bodies.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">globe valve body</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">corpo de válvula globo</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A valve body that has a globular geometry designed to accommodate the perpendicular flow path and disc closure mechanism characteristic of globe valve operation.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um corpo de válvula que possui geometria globular projetada para acomodar o caminho de fluxo perpendicular e o mecanismo de fechamento por disco característico da operação de válvula globo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every globe valve body is a valve body that has globular geometry for perpendicular flow path accommodation.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1776"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000078"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000347">
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every shaker is an assembly that has the capability of shaking and contains a vibration mechanism and a shaking element.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2919"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A shaker is an assembly that bears a shaking function, capable of producing vibrating or oscillating motion for material processing, agitation, or separation.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um agitador é um conjunto que possui uma função de agitação, capaz de produzir movimento vibratório ou oscilatório para processamento, agitação ou separação de materiais.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">Shaker(x) ↔ Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(ShakingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SHAKER&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that has the capability of &lt;SHAKING&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A piece of drilling equipment, usually with a vibrating screen, where drill cuttings are removed from the flowing mud.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] Abbreviation for shale shaker, the primary and probably most important device on the rig for removing drilled solids from the mud.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">agitador</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">shaker</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000246">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um detector é um instrumento que possui uma função de detecção, permitindo-lhe detectar estados, substâncias ou fenômenos e produzir sinais baseados na detecção.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A detector is an instrument that bears a detection function, enabling it to sense states, substances, or phenomena and produce signals based on the detection.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Detector(x) ↔ Instrument(x) ∧ ∃f(DetectionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">detector</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">detector</rdfs:label>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b893"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every detector is an instrument that has a detection function and has component parts including a sensing element and signal generation device.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DETECTOR&gt; is an &lt;INSTRUMENTATION FUNCTION&gt; that has a capability of &lt;DETECTING&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[isa5_1] a device that is used to detect the presence of something, such as flammable or toxic gases or discrete parts; see also primary element and sensor.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A sensor or receiver, such as a geophone or hydrophone, gravimeter or magnetometer.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that is an assembly of a sensing element and necessary ancillary devices making it able of detecting a state, e.g. pressure, temperature, or detect the presence of a selected substance, and produce a signal based on the detection.</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2386">
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2387"/>
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2381"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/DifferentialPressureMeasurementProcess">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b993"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b983"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b984"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b994"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">differential pressure measurement process</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de medição de pressão diferencial</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a differential pressure measuring element senses the pressure difference between two fluid inputs, producing a mechanical deflection or signal proportional to the differential pressure for measurement purposes.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/RotationalEnergyTransferFunction">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2786"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/DesignedFunction"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2785"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A DesignedFunction that is realized in a RotationalEnergyTransferProcess and that consists in the capacity to transfer mechanical energy through rotational motion within a machine assembly.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de transferência de energia rotacional</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">rotational energy transfer function</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2226">
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2227"/>
