  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000313">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">mill</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">moinho</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um moinho é um conjunto que possui uma função de processamento de material para reduzir o tamanho de partículas ou modificar materiais sólidos através de operações mecânicas de moagem, corte ou trituração.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A mill is an assembly that bears a material processing function to reduce particle size or modify solid materials through mechanical grinding, cutting, or crushing operations.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A mill is usually used to remove junk in the hole or to grind away all or part of a casing string.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A cutting tool used to grind up metal, dress off a fish, or open up a window for a kick-off.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;MILL&gt; is a &lt;FACILITY&gt; that consists of the land, buildings, machinery, apparatus, and fixtures, mostly employed in &lt;MANUFACTURING&gt; of discrete &lt;COMMODITY MATERIAL&gt;s</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every mill is an assembly that has the function to process materials, and every assembly that has the function to process materials is a mill.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2221"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Mill(x) ↔ (Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(MaterialProcessingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PipelineConnection">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pipeline connection</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">conexão de pipeline</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000378">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;WIRELINE&gt; is an &lt;ELECTRICAL CABLE&gt; used to lower tools into and transmit data about the conditions of the wellbore called wireline logs. Usually consisting of braided cables, wirelines are used to perform wireline logging, as well.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] Related to any aspect of logging that employs an electrical cable to lower tools into the borehole and to transmit data. Wireline logging is distinct from measurements-while-drilling (MWD) and mud logging.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] schlumberger wireline, well logging, well intervention, slickline, formation evaluation</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um wireline é um cabo elétrico que possui uma função de perfilagem wireline para descer ferramentas em poços e transmitir dados sobre as condições do poço.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A wireline is an electrical cable that bears a wireline logging function for lowering tools into wellbores and transmitting data about wellbore conditions.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every wireline is an electrical cable that has the function to lower tools into wellbores and transmit logging data signals to the surface.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">wireline</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">wireline</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Wireline(x) ↔ ElectricalCable(x) ∧ ∃f (WirelineLoggingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b3491"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000262">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">electrical connection</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">conexão elétrica</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(ElectricalConnection(x) ↔ (MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃f(ElectricalConductionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃p(ElectricalConductionProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p) ∧ ∃y(ElectricalApparatus(y) ∧ has_participant_at_some_time(p,y)))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma conexão elétrica é um MaterialArtifact que possui uma ElectricalConductionFunction e que fornece um caminho para a corrente elétrica passar de um aparelho elétrico para outro.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An electrical connection is a MaterialArtifact that bears an ElectricalConductionFunction and that provides a pathway for electrical current to pass from one electrical apparatus to another.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1203"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every electrical connection is a material artifact that bears an electrical conduction function and participates in processes involving electrical apparatus.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;ELECTRICAL CONNECTION&gt; is a &lt;DirectConnection&gt; for letting pass a &lt;CURRENT&gt; from one &lt;ELECTRICAL APPARATUS&gt; to another</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FluidDistributionProcess">
