  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000274">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A system that burns waste in an elevated flame in the open air.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[DEXPI] An artefact and waste gas emitter that is intended to burn waste gas in secure distance from the plant or platform.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A burner on a remote line used for disposal of hydrocarbons during clean-up, emergency shut downs and for disposal of small volume waste streams of mixed gasses that cannot easily or safely be separated.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] The burning of unwanted gas through a pipe (also called a flare).</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FLARE&gt; is a &lt;BURNER&gt; that has a capability of &lt;FLARING&gt;</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">flare</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flare</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Flare(x) ↔ (Burner(x) ∧ ∃f (WasteGasDisposalFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A flare is a burner that safely disposes of unwanted gases through controlled combustion at an elevated location.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um flare é um queimador que descarta com segurança gases indesejados através de combustão controlada em local elevado.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every flare is a burner that bears a waste gas disposal function and has component parts flare tip, flare stack, and pilot system.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1405"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/LevelMeasurementAndTransmissionProcess">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2143"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2142"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2141"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">level measurement and transmission process</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de medição e transmissão de nível</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/EnclosureProcess">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a structural body provides containment and directional guidance for fluid flow while housing internal valve components that control the flow.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a casing provides protective containment around mechanical components while enabling controlled fluid passage through designed openings and maintaining pressure boundaries.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a housing structure provides physical containment and environmental protection for internal components, shielding them from external conditions such as moisture, dust, mechanical impact, and temperature variations.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a casing provides protective containment around internal components, maintaining their operational environment and structural integrity while allowing controlled access for maintenance.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a structural housing provides containment and protection for mechanical components, creating a defined boundary between internal mechanisms and the external environment.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a housing artifact creates and maintains a protective boundary around internal components, simultaneously providing structural support and environmental separation.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a body or housing artifact provides structural containment and protection for internal mechanical components or assemblies.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a housing or casing provides containment and protection for internal components, maintaining separation between the internal mechanism and external environment.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b403"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1861"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b3247"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b616"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b3246"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b428"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b402"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1774"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b401"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b429"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1862"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b617"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1775"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de proteção e invólucro</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">enclosure process</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000297">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Housing SubClassOf Assembly and (bearerOf some EnclosureFunction) and (bearerOf some SupportFunction)</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um Assembly que possui tanto uma EnclosureFunction quanto uma SupportFunction, fornecendo limites protetivos ao redor de componentes internos enquanto os suporta estruturalmente.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An Assembly that bears both an EnclosureFunction and a SupportFunction, providing protective boundaries around internal components while structurally supporting them.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;HOUSING&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and an &lt;ENCLOSURE&gt; and a &lt;SUPPORT&gt; that, next to separation, also provides support</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] An enclosure that also provides support.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] The outside steel case of a cartridge or a sonde in a wireline logging tool.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Housing(x) → Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f₁(EnclosureFunction(f₁) ∧ bearerOf(x,f₁)) ∧ ∃f₂(SupportFunction(f₂) ∧ bearerOf(x,f₂)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type based on physical configuration. Under OWA, sufficient conditions would force any assembly with enclosure and support functions to be classified as a standard housing, potentially misclassifying specialized equipment with housing-like properties but different maintenance categories.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">carcaça</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">housing</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1863"/>
  </rdf:Description>
