  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000217">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;BOILER&gt; is a &lt;HEATER&gt; that brings a &lt;LIQUID&gt; to its boiling point</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[DEXPI] A that brings a liquid to its boiling point.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] An indirect contact heat exchanger that is intended to heat a liquid.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Boiler(x) ↔ Heater(x) ∧ ∃f(BoilingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">caldeira</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">boiler</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma caldeira é um aquecedor que leva um líquido ao seu ponto de ebulição através de troca de calor por contato indireto, produzindo vapor.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A boiler is a heater that brings a liquid to its boiling point through indirect contact heat exchange, producing steam or vapor.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every boiler is a heater that bears a BoilingFunction and has component parts including a steam drum and heat exchange surface.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b292"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000289">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1729"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000072"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1725"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1726"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1727"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1728"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every gear pump is a pump that has as component part at all times a gear mechanism and a pump casing, and bears a pumping function.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A rotary pump that contains gear teeth within an casing or enclosure to transport liquid at relatively high back pressures and by which gear meshing serves as reverse flow seal.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;GEAR PUMP&gt; is a &lt;ROTARY PUMP&gt; that contains gear teeth within an casing or enclosure to transport liquid at relatively high back pressures</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">bomba de engrenagem</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">gear pump</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A gear pump is a pump that contains gear teeth within a casing or enclosure to transport liquid at relatively high back pressures through meshing action.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma bomba de engrenagem é uma bomba que contém dentes de engrenagem dentro de um invólucro ou carcaça para transportar líquido em pressões de retorno relativamente altas através de ação de engrenamento.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (GearPump(x) → Pump(x) ∧ ∃g,c (GearMechanism(g) ∧ PumpCasing(c) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,g) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,c)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions for this constructive type. While the gear mechanism is definitionally necessary for gear pumps, making it sufficient under OWA could lead to false positives - any complex equipment containing gears (like gearboxes with integrated pumps or multi-function units) might be incorrectly classified as standard gear pumps for maintenance purposes.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000302">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">impeller</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">impulsor</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Impeller(x) → Assembly(x) ∧ ∃v,h(RotatingVanes(v) ∧ Hub(h) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,v) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,h) ∧ ∃m(RotationalMotion(m) ∧ participatesIn(x,m)) ∧ ∃f(EnergyTransferFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every impeller is an assembly that has rotating vanes and a hub as component parts at all times, participates in rotational motion, and bears an energy transfer function.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1954"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1956"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1955"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;IMPELLER&gt; is a &lt;MECHANICAL TO MECHANICAL ENERGY CONVERTER&gt; that is an assembly of rotating vanes within an enclosure which is used to impart energy to or derive energy from a fluid through dynamic force</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[DEXPI] An energy converter component that is an assembly of rotating vanes within an enclosure which is used to impart energy to or derive energy from a fluid through dynamic force (from ``_).</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] In electromagnetics or electrical circuit theory, the ratio of voltage to current when these are represented by phasor quantities in alternating current circuits. (A phasor is a complex number that represents the amplitude and phase of a quantity that varies sinusoidally in time.) Electrical impedance, also symbolized by Z, is a complex number that has the same units (ohms) as resistivity.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] The rotating pump component that drives the fluid in a centrifugal pump.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive classification based on physical mechanism. Under OWA, defining sufficient conditions for the rotating vane assembly could lead to false positives where other rotating equipment with vanes (like turbine rotors or fan assemblies) might be incorrectly classified as impellers when they should remain in their specific equipment categories.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An impeller is an assembly consisting of rotating vanes mounted on a hub that transfers energy to or from fluids through dynamic rotational force within an enclosure.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um impulsor é um conjunto que consiste em pás rotativas montadas em um cubo que transfere energia para ou de fluidos através de força rotacional dinâmica dentro de um invólucro.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000282">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FUSE&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;PROTECTOR&gt; and an &lt;ELECTRICAL ELEMENT&gt; that opens the circuit in which it is inserted by breaking the current when this exceeds a given value for a sufficient time</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that by the fusing of one or more of its specially designed and proportioned components, opens the circuit in which it is inserted by breaking the current when this exceeds a given value for a sufficient time.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A physical object that by the fusing of one or more of its specially designed and proportioned components, opens the circuit in which it is inserted by breaking the current when this exceeds a given value for a sufficient time.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um fusível é um equipamento elétrico que protege circuitos interrompendo o fluxo de corrente através do derretimento intencional de um elemento fusível quando a corrente excede valores especificados por uma duração suficiente.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A fuse is an electrical equipment that protects circuits by interrupting current flow through the intentional melting of a fusible element when current exceeds specified values for a sufficient duration.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">fuse</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">fusível</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Fuse(x) ↔ ElectricalEquipment(x) ∧ ∃f(CircuitProtectionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃e(FuseElement(e) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,e)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every fuse is an electrical equipment that bears a circuit protection function and has a fuse element that melts under overcurrent conditions.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1612"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b763">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/DeaerationProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
