  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000284">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;GAS DETECTOR&gt; is a &lt;DETECTOR&gt; and a &lt;GAS DETECTING INSTRUMENT&gt; using a &lt;GAS DETECTING MEASURING ELEMENT&gt; that is intended to sense the presence of a specified concentration of a gas</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A detector that is intended to sense the presence of a specified concentration of a gas.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A detector that is intended to sense the presence of a specified concentration of a gas.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">gas detector</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">detector de gás</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A gas detector is a detector that has the designed function to sense the presence of a specified concentration of a gas.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um detector de gás é um detector que tem a função projetada de detectar a presença de uma concentração especificada de um gás.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every gas detector is a detector that bears a GasDetectionFunction and has a GasDetectingMeasuringElement as component part at all times.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(GasDetector(x) ↔ (Detector(x) ∧ ∃f(GasDetectionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1640"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/DryingFunction">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1112"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1113"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/DesignedFunction"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de secagem</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">drying function</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000322">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pipe bend</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">curva de tubo</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2418"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2419"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000321"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;PIPE BEND&gt; is a &lt;PIPING COMPONENT&gt; that is intended to change piping direction with a non-standard radius</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] An 'artefact' that is intended to change piping direction with a non-standard radius</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that is used to change piping direction with a non-standard radius.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions for this constructive type. While the curved geometry with non-standard radius is distinctive, making it sufficient under OWA could force classification of complex piping assemblies or custom manifolds containing bent sections into this maintenance category inappropriately.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma curva de tubo é um tubo que possui geometria curvada para mudar a direção da tubulação com um raio não padrão.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A pipe bend is a pipe that has a curved geometry to change piping direction with a non-standard radius.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every pipe bend is a pipe that has curved geometry and has non-standard bend radius.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (PipeBend(x) → Pipe(x) ∧ ∃g (CurvedGeometry(g) ∧ hasQuality(x,g)) ∧ ∃r (NonStandardBendRadius(r) ∧ hasQuality(x,r)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2926">
    <rdf:rest rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#nil"/>
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2922"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000344">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SCRAPER&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that is capable of &lt;SCRAPING&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object intended to mechanically remove a deposit from a surface.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] Also called a pig, a device with blades or brushes inserted in a pipeline for cleaning purposes.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A device that cuts through paraffin, asphaltenes, etc. inside the pipe. Run on wireline.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every scraper is a material artifact that has a scraping function, and every material artifact that has a scraping function is a scraper.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A scraper is a material artifact that bears a scraping function for mechanically removing deposits, debris, or contaminants from surfaces.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um raspador é um artefato material que possui uma função de raspagem para remover mecanicamente depósitos, detritos ou contaminantes de superfícies.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">scraper</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">raspador</rdfs:label>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2837"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Scraper(x) ↔ (MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃f(ScrapingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
