  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000290">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um Assembly que porta uma PowerTransmissionFunction e que possui dentes circunferenciais para engajamento mecânico positivo com engrenagens ou cremalheiras correspondentes para transmitir movimento rotacional e potência.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An Assembly that bears a PowerTransmissionFunction and that has circumferential teeth for positive mechanical engagement with mating gears or racks to transmit rotational motion and power.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">gear wheel</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">roda dentada</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1737"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000121"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;GEAR WHEEL&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;TRANSMITTER(force)&gt; and that is a toothed wheel usend in conjunction with another, or with a rack, to transmit motion</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(GearWheel(x) → Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(PowerTransmissionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃t(Tooth(t) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,t)) ∧ ∃w(WheelBody(w) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,w)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">GearWheel SubClassOf Assembly and (bearerOf some PowerTransmissionFunction) and (hasComponentPartAtAllTimes some Tooth) and (hasComponentPartAtAllTimes some WheelBody)</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive differentia based on physical structure (toothed geometry). Under OWA, asserting equivalence could force classification of complex hybrid mechanisms or specialized toothed components that should not be categorized as standard gear wheels for maintenance purposes.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
