  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000268">
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every filter press is a filter that has a pressure mechanism as part and participates in mechanical compression processes.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">filter press</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">prensa filtrante</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] Usually a DE filter.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FILTER PRESS&gt; is a &lt;FILTER&gt; and a &lt;PRESS(machine)&gt; intended to separate substance through compression</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A pressurized cell, fitted with a filter medium, used for evaluating filtration characteristics of a drilling fluid while it is either static or stirred.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions because this is classified as 'both' functional and constructive. The structural differentia (pressure mechanism and compression process) involves specific mechanical configurations that are harder to make sufficient under Open World Assumption without detailed engineering specifications.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A filter press is a filter that applies mechanical compression force to enhance the separation of substances through a pressurized filtration process.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma prensa filtrante é um filtro que aplica força de compressão mecânica para melhorar a separação de substâncias através de um processo de filtração pressurizada.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1318"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1321"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1320"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1319"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000081"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(FilterPress(x) → Filter(x) ∧ ∃p(PressureMechanism(p) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,p)) ∧ ∃proc(MechanicalCompressionProcess(proc) ∧ participatesIn(x,proc)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000251">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b995"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(DifferentialPressureMeasuringElement(x) ↔ (PressureElement(x) ∧ ∃f(DifferentialPressureMeasurementFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A pressure element that bears a differential pressure measurement function and that consists in sensing the pressure difference between two fluid media or connection points to enable measurement of differential pressure through mechanical deflection proportional to the pressure difference.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um elemento de pressão que porta uma função de medição de pressão diferencial e que consiste em detectar a diferença de pressão entre duas mídias fluidas ou pontos de conexão para permitir a medição de pressão diferencial através de deflexão mecânica proporcional à diferença de pressão.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">elemento medidor de pressão diferencial</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">differential pressure measuring element</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">DifferentialPressureMeasuringElement equivalentTo PressureElement and bearerOf some DifferentialPressureMeasurementFunction</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DIFFERENTIAL PRESSURE MEASURING ELEMENT&gt; is a &lt;PRESSURE MEASURING ELEMENT&gt; for the measurement of &lt;DIFFERENTIAL PRESSURE&gt;</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PolyphaseElectricalSignal">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">polyphase electrical signal</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">sinal polifásico elétrico</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000275">
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(FlareTip(x) ↔ Burner(x) ∧ ∃f(WasteGasDisposalFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FLARE TIP&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;BURNER&gt; that burns gas emitted from a process into the atmosphere</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A burner that burns gas emitted from a process into the atmosphere.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A burner that burns gas emitted from a process into the atmosphere.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every flare tip is a burner that has the function to dispose of waste gas from processes by burning it into the atmosphere</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A flare tip is a burner that specifically burns waste gas emitted from industrial processes and discharges the combustion products into the atmosphere.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um queimador de flare é um queimador que especificamente queima gás residual emitido de processos industriais e descarrega os produtos de combustão na atmosfera.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flare tip</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">queimador de flare</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1431"/>
  </rdf:Description>
