  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000225">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000084"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b447"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b446"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b448"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b445"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">centrifuge</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">centrífuga</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CENTRIFUGE&gt; is a &lt;MACHINE&gt; and a &lt;SEPARATOR&gt; that uses centrifugal force to separate phases of different densities</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] An item of solids-removal equipment that removes fine and ultrafine solids.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A device that separates materials by density through a centrifugal motion.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A 'separator' and 'machine' that uses centrifugal force to separate phases of different densities.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that uses centrifugal force to separate phases of different densities.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A centrifuge is a separator that uses centrifugal force generated by a rotating drum to separate phases of different densities.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma centrífuga é um separador que usa força centrífuga gerada por um tambor rotativo para separar fases de diferentes densidades.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every centrifuge is a separator that has a rotating drum as component part and participates in centrifugal force processes.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Centrifuge(x) → Separator(x) ∧ ∃d (RotatingDrum(d) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,d)) ∧ ∃p (CentrifugalForceProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Although functionally defined as a separator, the constructive differentia (centrifugal mechanism) makes sufficient conditions complex under OWA. Any equipment with a rotating drum could potentially be classified as a centrifuge even if designed for other purposes (mixing, drying, etc.). Starting with necessary conditions protects against false positives.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b813">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:intersectionOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b819"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/GasDetectionFunction">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de detecção de gás</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">gas detection function</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1637"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/DetectionFunction"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1636"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000377">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b3466"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] The mechanical connection between the tree and the casing. May house tubular hangers, annular access valves. It is connected to the casing by welding, threads, hydraulic forming or set screws.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] The wellhead is assembled from, or incorporates facilities for, the upper casing and tubing hangers. This effectively provides the upper termination of the wellbore and provides a mounting position for the surface flow-control equipment or Christmas tree.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;WELLHEAD&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; that is the top of the casing of a production oil well including the attached control and flow valves</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] The system of spools, valves and assorted adapters that provide pressure control of a production well.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Wellhead(x) ↔ Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(WellSurfaceControlFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃h(CasingHanger(h) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,h)) ∧ ∃w(Wellbore(w) ∧ hasConnectionTo(x,w)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um cabeçal de poço é um conjunto que porta uma função de controle superficial do poço e fornece a interface estrutural e de controle entre um poço e os equipamentos de superfície.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A wellhead is an assembly that bears a well surface control function and provides the structural and control interface between a wellbore and surface equipment.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every wellhead is an assembly that bears a well surface control function and has component parts including casing hangers and connection to wellbore</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">cabeçal de poço</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">wellhead</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000306">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000346"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2032"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type based on physical configuration as energy entrance point. Under OWA, defining sufficient conditions could lead to false positives where any shaft receiving external energy input would be classified as a standard input shaft, even specialized or hybrid configurations that should remain in different maintenance categories.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;INPUT SHAFT&gt; is a &lt;SHAFT&gt; that is the entrance of mechanical energy and driven by an external energy source.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">An InputShaft is a Shaft that participates in mechanical energy reception and is connected to an external energy source.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(InputShaft(x) → Shaft(x) ∧ ∃p(MechanicalEnergyReceptionProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)) ∧ ∃s(ExternalEnergySource(s) ∧ connectedTo(x,s)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">eixo de entrada</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">input shaft</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An input shaft is a shaft that serves as the entrance point for mechanical energy from an external energy source in a power transmission system.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um eixo de entrada é um eixo que serve como ponto de entrada para energia mecânica de uma fonte de energia externa em um sistema de transmissão de potência.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b541">
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b535"/>
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b542"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000323">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2424"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2426"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000321"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2425"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">cotovelo de tubulação</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pipe elbow</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um cotovelo de tubulação é uma tubulação que possui geometria curva permitindo mudanças direcionais em trechos de tubulação entre 0 e 135 graus.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A pipe elbow is a pipe that has curved geometry enabling directional changes in pipe runs between 0 and 135 degrees.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every pipe elbow is a pipe that has curved geometry and enables directional change capacity between 0 and 135 degrees.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions for this constructive type protects against false positives under OWA. Any curved piping component would be forcibly classified as a pipe elbow under equivalent axioms, including specialized equipment like coiled tubing, serpentine heat exchanger tubes, or custom manifold sections that contain curved passages but should not be asserted into the standard pipe elbow maintenance category.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (PipeElbow(x) → (Pipe(x) ∧ ∃g(CurvedGeometry(g) ∧ hasGeometricProperty(x,g)) ∧ ∃p(DirectionalChangeCapacity(p) ∧ hasProperty(x,p))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;PIPE ELBOW&gt; is a &lt;PIPING COMPONENT&gt; and an &lt;ELBOW&gt; that is intended to make a change in the direction of a pipe run between 0 and 135 degrees</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] An 'elbow' and an 'artefact' that is intended to make a change in the direction of a pipe run between 0 and 135 degrees.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000372">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b3389"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b3388"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;VALVE STEM&gt; is a &lt;VALVE COMPONENT&gt; and a &lt;TRANSMITTER(force)&gt; that is a rod or shaft which is transmitting motion from an operator to the closure member of a valve</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(ValveStem(x) → Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(ForceTransmissionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃s(ValveStemSeal(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">ValveStem SubClassOf Assembly and bearerOf some ForceTransmissionFunction and hasComponentPartAtAllTimes some ValveStemSeal</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um Assembly que porta uma ForceTransmissionFunction e que tem um selo de haste de válvula como parte componente, especificamente projetado para transmitir movimento de um operador de válvula para o membro de fechamento da válvula.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An Assembly that bears a ForceTransmissionFunction and that has a valve stem seal as a component part, specifically designed to transmit motion from a valve operator to the valve closure member.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">haste de válvula</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">valve stem</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type defined by physical structure (rod/shaft mechanism). Under Open World Assumption, sufficient conditions would force any assembly with a valve stem seal and force transmission function to be classified as a valve stem, which could include complex multi-component assemblies, manifolds, or specialized valve mechanisms that contain these elements but should not be asserted into the standard valve stem maintenance category.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ScrapingElement">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">scraping element</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">elemento de raspagem</rdfs:label>
