  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000276">
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(FlashDrum(x) ↔ Separator(x) ∧ ∃f(FlashVaporizationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A tank or vessel in which a process stream is charged or pumped and where lighter products flash off or vaporize and are drawn off at the top. The remainder heavier fractions are drawn off at the bottom of the vessel.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FLASH DRUM&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;VESSEL&gt; in which a process stream is charged or pumped and where lighter products flash off or vaporize and are drawn off at the top. The remainer heavier fractions are drawn off at the bottom of the vessel</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um tambor de flash é um separador que realiza vaporização flash para separar componentes mais leves (que vaporizam e são retirados no topo) de componentes mais pesados (que permanecem líquidos e são retirados no fundo).</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A flash drum is a separator that performs flash vaporization to separate lighter components (which vaporize and are drawn off at the top) from heavier components (which remain liquid and are drawn off at the bottom).</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every flash drum is a separator that bears a flash vaporization function and has a vapor outlet, liquid outlet, and feed inlet.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1458"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">tambor de flash</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flash drum</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b870">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasInput"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/MaterialEntity"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/InformationBearingArtifact">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">information bearing artifact</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">artefato de informação de mancal</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000325">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2446"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2445"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2448"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2447"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000321"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] An 'artefact' that has three piping ends in T-shape, including a branch at 90 degrees.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that has three piping ends in T-shape, including a branch at 90 degrees.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;PIPE TEE&gt; is a &lt;PIPING COMPONENT&gt; and a &lt;PIPING NETWORK NODE&gt; and three piping ends in T-shape, including a branch at 90 degrees</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every pipe tee is a pipe that has exactly three fluid ports arranged in T-configuration and bears a fluid conduction function</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(PipeTee(x) → Pipe(x) ∧ ∃p1,p2,p3(BranchPort(p1) ∧ RunPort(p2) ∧ RunPort(p3) ∧ hasPartAtAllTimes(x,p1) ∧ hasPartAtAllTimes(x,p2) ∧ hasPartAtAllTimes(x,p3) ∧ perpendicularTo(p1,p2) ∧ perpendicularTo(p1,p3)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pipe tee</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">tê de tubulação</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A pipe tee is a pipe fitting that has three fluid ports arranged in T-shaped configuration, with one branch port perpendicular to two run ports, designed to realize fluid conduction function through flow division or combination.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um tê de tubulação é uma conexão de tubulação que possui três portas de fluido dispostas em configuração em formato de T, com uma porta de ramal perpendicular a duas portas de passagem, projetada para realizar função de condução de fluido através de divisão ou combinação de fluxo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions for this constructive type. The T-shaped geometric configuration with three specific ports is a structural differentia that is harder to make sufficient under OWA. Custom manifolds or complex fittings might contain T-shaped passages but should not be automatically classified as standard pipe tees without domain expert validation.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PipeWall">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pipe wall</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">parede de tubo</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2634">
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2635"/>
    <rdf:first rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000157"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b474">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FluidPortion"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasInput"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FlowModificationFunction">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A FlowControlFunction that is realized in a FlowModificationProcess and that consists in altering the characteristics of fluid flow (such as velocity profile, turbulence, pressure drop pattern, or flow distribution) without primarily controlling the flow rate or direction.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1536"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1537"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000026"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de modificação de fluxo</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flow modification function</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/CombustionChamber">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
