  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000265">
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (ExpansionJoint(x) ↔ (MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃f(ThermalExpansionAccommodationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃g(FlexibilityFunction(g) ∧ hasFunction(x,g))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] Flexible joint between two pipes to receive expansion from the pipes.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A device or completion component designed to enable relative movement between two fixed assemblies in the event of thermal expansion or contraction.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;EXPANSION JOINT&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;JOINT&gt; that makes allowance for thermal expansion of the parts joined without distortion</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A device in a length of pipe that allows some pipe length expansion or contraction.</skos:definition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1251"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">expansion joint</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">junta de expansão</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma junta de expansão é um artefato material que possui a função projetada de acomodar expansão e contração térmica entre componentes conectados através de flexibilidade inerente, mantendo a integridade estrutural.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An expansion joint is a material artifact that bears the designed function of accommodating thermal expansion and contraction between connected components through inherent flexibility while maintaining structural integrity.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every expansion joint is a material artifact that bears a thermal expansion accommodation function and has a flexibility function, and every material artifact that bears a thermal expansion accommodation function and has a flexibility function is an expansion joint.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2359">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FluidPortion"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasSpecifiedOutput"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ElectricalSwitch">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">interruptor elétrico</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">electrical switch</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000234">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um controlador é um instrumento que possui uma função de controle, regulando automaticamente uma variável controlada ao medi-la, comparar com um valor de referência e gerar sinais de saída para reduzir o desvio.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A controller is an instrument that bears a control function, automatically regulating a controlled variable by measuring it, comparing with a reference value, and generating output signals to reduce deviation.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b679"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every controller is an instrument that has the function to control a process variable by automatic feedback regulation</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">controlador</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">controller</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A regulator that operates automatically to affect a controlled variable by comparing the value of the controlled variable with the value of a reference variable in order to reduce the difference between them.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A device that measures a controlled variable, compares it with a predetermined setting and signals an actuator to readjust the opening of a valve.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CONTROLLER&gt; is an &lt;INSTRUMENTATION FUNCTION&gt; that is capable of &lt;CONTROLLING&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[isa5_1] a device having an output that varies to regulate a controlled variable in a specified manner that may be a self-contained analog or digital instrument, or may be the equivalent of such an instrument in a shared- control system.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Controller(x) ↔ Instrument(x) ∧ ∃f(ControlFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1915">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000059"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasInput"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000209">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A cooler that is intended to use air as the cooling medium.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;AIR COOLED HEAT EXCHANGER&gt; is a &lt;HEAT EXCHANGER&gt; and an &lt;AIR COOLED OBJECT&gt; and a &lt;FLUID CONTAINER&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A cooler that is intended to use air as the cooling medium.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every air cooled heat exchanger is a heat exchanger that has component parts including an air fin system and tube bundle, and participates in air cooling processes.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b80"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b82"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b83"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b81"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000092"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(AirCooledHeatExchanger(x) → HeatExchanger(x) ∧ ∃y(AirFinSystem(y) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,y)) ∧ ∃z(TubeBundle(z) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,z)) ∧ ∃p(AirCoolingProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um trocador de calor resfriado a ar é um trocador de calor que possui superfícies aletadas de resfriamento a ar e usa ar ambiente como meio de resfriamento para transferir energia térmica de fluidos de processo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An air cooled heat exchanger is a heat exchanger that has finned air cooling surfaces and uses ambient air as the cooling medium to transfer thermal energy from process fluids.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">air cooled heat exchanger</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">trocador de calor resfriado a ar</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Under the Open World Assumption, defining air cooling constructively as sufficient conditions could lead to false positives. Complex hybrid equipment or specialized configurations with air cooling components might be inappropriately classified. Starting with necessary conditions allows for proper validation by domain experts before upgrading to equivalence.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
