  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000346">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2913"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2911"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2912"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2914"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every shaft is an assembly that transmits power through rotation and has shaft keys, shaft seals, and shaft sleeves as essential components.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um Assembly que porta uma PowerTransmissionFunction e que possui partes componentes incluindo chavetas de eixo para transmissão de torque e vedações de eixo para prevenção de vazamento, servindo como o elemento rotativo central em máquinas rotativas.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An Assembly that bears a PowerTransmissionFunction and that has component parts including shaft keys for torque transmission and shaft seals for leakage prevention, serving as the core rotating element in rotating machinery.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">shaft</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">eixo</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Shaft(x) → Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(PowerTransmissionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃k(ShaftKey(k) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,k)) ∧ ∃s(ShaftSeal(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s)) ∧ ∃l(ShaftSleeve(l) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,l)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SHAFT&gt; is an &lt;ENGINE COMPONENT&gt; that is the core rotating element on which the rotating parts are mounted and through which energy is either transmitted from the prime mover or generated in case of a driver.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive classification based on physical structure. Under OWA, sufficient conditions for shaft identity could lead to false positives - any assembly with a shaft key and rotational motion might be classified as a shaft rather than a more specific equipment type that contains a shaft. The structural differentia provides necessary conditions while allowing domain experts to validate sufficiency.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b817">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/AirIntake"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PneumaticEnergyConversionProcess">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2515"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2513"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2514"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pneumatic energy conversion process</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de conversão de energia pneumática</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ForceTransmissionFunction">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de transmissão de força</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">force transmission function</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b3384"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b3385"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/DesignedFunction"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A DesignedFunction that is realized in a ForceTransmissionProcess and that consists in transmitting mechanical force or motion from one component to another through direct physical coupling.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000301">
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Hydrocyclone(x) ↔ Separator(x) ∧ ∃c(ConicalSection(c) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,c)) ∧ ∃p(CentrifugalSeparationProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A cone shaped device for separating fluids and the solids dispersed in fluids.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] An item of solids-control equipment consisting of an inverted cone, the mud being fed tangentially into the upper (larger diameter) part.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;HYDROCYCLONE&gt; is a &lt;CYCLONE&gt; and a &lt;CYLINDRICAL VESSEL&gt;, intended to separate a fluid by hydraulic forces</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um hidrociclone é um separador que separa misturas de fluidos usando forças centrífugas geradas por fluxo tangencial através de uma câmara cônica.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A hydrocyclone is a separator that separates fluid mixtures using centrifugal forces generated by tangential flow through a conical chamber.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every hydrocyclone is a separator that has a conical section as component part at all times and participates in centrifugal separation processes.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">hydrocyclone</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">hidrociclone</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1935"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2704">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FluidPortion"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasSpecifiedOutput"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2355">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PigReceivingProcess"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2005">
