  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000371">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">assento de válvula</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">valve seat</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (ValveSeat(x) → (MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃y(Valve(y) ∧ partOf(x,y)) ∧ ∃z(ValveClosureMember(z) ∧ adjacentTo(x,z)) ∧ ∃q(SealingSurfaceQuality(q) ∧ bearerOf(x,q))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">ValveSeat ⊑ MaterialArtifact ⊓ ∃partOf.Valve ⊓ ∃adjacentTo.ValveClosureMember ⊓ ∃bearerOf.SealingSurfaceQuality</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;VALVE SEAT&gt; is a &lt;VALVE COMPONENT&gt; that is the part of a valve against which the closure member bears to provide shut-off and throughput of process fluids flows</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b3383"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A MaterialArtifact that is part of a valve and that provides the seating surface against which the closure member bears to achieve shut-off and control of process fluid flow.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um MaterialArtifact que é parte de uma válvula e que fornece a superfície de assentamento contra a qual o membro de fechamento se apoia para alcançar o fechamento e controle do fluxo de fluido de processo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Valve seat is a constructive type defined by its structural configuration and interface role. Under the Open World Assumption, making this an equivalence class could lead to false positives where any artifact that is part of a valve and adjacent to a closure member gets classified as a valve seat, even if it serves a different structural role (such as guides, stops, or supports).</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
