  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000369">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A distillation column intended to withstand outside pressure.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;VACUUM COLUMN&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;DISTILLATION COLUMN&gt; intended to withstand outside pressure</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A distillation column intended to withstand outside pressure</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(VacuumColumn(x) → DistillationColumn(x) ∧ ∃q(VacuumPressureResistanceQuality(q) ∧ bearerOf(x,q)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b3350"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b3349"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b3351"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000255"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type based on structural capability. Under OWA, defining sufficient conditions for vacuum-capable design would be complex and could lead to false positives. The structural differentia (vacuum resistance) requires domain expert validation of what constitutes adequate vacuum design capability.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every vacuum column is a distillation column that bears a vacuum pressure resistance quality.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">vacuum column</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">coluna de vácuo</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A vacuum column is a distillation column that is designed to withstand outside pressure during vacuum operation.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma coluna de vácuo é uma coluna de destilação projetada para resistir à pressão externa durante operação sob vácuo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2452">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FluidTransportProcess"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b12">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000043"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasSpecifiedOutput"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2859">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/GasInlet"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b3176">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000201"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000318">
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(PigLauncher(x) ↔ (Vessel(x) ∧ ∃f(PigLaunchingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃c(PipelineConnection(c) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,c))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A pressure vessel intended for sending a pig into a pipeline.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;PIG LAUNCHER&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that is capable of &lt;LAUNCHING&gt; a &lt;PIPE PIG&gt; into a pipeline</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A chamber connected to a pipeline intended for sending pigs into the pipeline.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">lançador de pig</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pig launcher</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every pig launcher is a vessel that has the function to launch pipeline pigs and has a pipeline connection component.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A pig launcher is a vessel that bears a pig launching function for inserting pipeline pigs into pipeline systems.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um lançador de pig é um vaso que possui função de lançamento de pig para inserir pigs de duto em sistemas de tubulação.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2342"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2403">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PipeWall"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000229">
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every chromatograph is a process analyzer that has the function of chromatographic analysis.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b531"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] An analysing instrument that applies the principle of chromatography to analyse the molecular composition of a substance.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CHROMATOGRAPH&gt; is a &lt;PROCESS ANALYSER&gt; that analyses the molecular composition of a substance</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um cromatógrafo é um analisador de processo que possui uma função de análise cromatográfica.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A chromatograph is a process analyzer that bears a chromatographic analysis function.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">cromatógrafo</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">chromatograph</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Chromatograph(x) ↔ ProcessAnalyzer(x) ∧ ∃f (ChromatographicAnalysisFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b3375">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FluidPortion"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasInput"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000206">
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000206"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b24"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">accumulator</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">acumulador</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object for storing energy, and which after discharge may be recharged.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A device used in a hydraulic system to store energy or, in some applications, dampen pressure fluctuations.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;ACCUMULATOR&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that has a capability of &lt;ACCUMULATING&gt; matter and/or energy</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A functional object capable of storing energy, and which after discharge may be recharged.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] In context of a pressure control device, accumulators are canisters of hydraulic fluid, pressurized with a nitrogen gas cap of sufficient pressure and volume to operate all the rams on a BOP in case of power failure to the BOP.                  In context of a processing plant, an accumulator is a vessel that receives and temporarily stores a liquid used in the feed stock or the processing of a feed stream in a gas plant or other processing facility.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um acumulador é um vaso que tem a função projetada de acumular (armazenar e liberar de forma controlada) energia ou matéria.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An accumulator is a vessel that has the designed function to accumulate (store and controllably release) energy or matter.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Accumulator(x) ↔ (Vessel(x) ∧ ∃f (AccumulationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every accumulator is a vessel that bears an accumulation function</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2940">
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2941"/>
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2936"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000288">
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(GearCasing(x) → casing(x) ∧ ∃y(GearMechanism(y) ∧ hasContent(x,y)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">carcaça de caixa de engrenagens</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">gear casing</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000222"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1720"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;GEAR CASING&gt; is a &lt;HOUSING&gt; that contains the internal components of a gear.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">GearCasing ⊑ casing ⊓ ∃hasContent.GearMechanism</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">This is a constructive type defined by its physical configuration as a specific type of casing. Under OWA, declaring equivalence could lead to over-classification where any casing containing gear-like components might be inappropriately classified as a standard gear casing, including custom enclosures or hybrid systems that should not fall into this maintenance category.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A casing that contains and houses the internal components of a gear mechanism, providing protective enclosure and structural support.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um invólucro que contém e abriga os componentes internos de um mecanismo de engrenagem, fornecendo invólucro protetor e suporte estrutural.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1030">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FluidPortion"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
