  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000375">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ppdm] A Well is a permitted or actual drilled hole in the ground designed to exchange (or facilitate the exchange of) fluids between a subsurface reservoir and the surface (or another reservoir), or to enable the detection and measurement of rock properties. Key concept: A physical Well is created each time the drill bit breaks the surface of the earth. Clarification: A Well is the parent of the Wellhead Stream(s), Well Origin, and all Well Components down hole from its Well Origin. A Well has a single Well Origin and all Wellbore(s) that extend from this Well Origin are parts of the Well. Re-entry through the same Well Origin for a Well that has not been plugged and abandoned does not create a new Well. A Well that has the same geographic coordinates as a previously existing plugged and abandoned, reclaimed or undrilled Well is a new Well. WB2-Cl2 Diagram Note: The Well depicted on page 3 groups multiple Well Components, including: one active Well WB2-C1 Origin (WO1), one inactive Wellbore (WB1), two active Wellbores (WB2, WB3), three inactive Wellbore Completions (WB1-C1, WB1-C2, WB1-C3) and three active Wellbore Completions (WB2-C1, WB3-C1, WB3-C2) and two active Wellbore Contact Intervals (WB2- CI1, WB2-CI2). ® Copyright 2014, PPDM Association. All Rights Reserved PAGE 4</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A well is a collection of (zero or more) holes drilled into the Earth for the purpose of either (1) finding or producing underground resources; or (2) providing services related to the production of underground resources.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;WELL&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that is arranged to obtain or produce from, or store or inject a material into, the earth</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">poço</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">well</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Well(x) ↔ EngineeredSystem(x) ∧ ∃f(SubsurfaceResourceInteractionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃w(Wellbore(w) ∧ hasComponentPartAtSomeTime(x,w)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A well is an engineered system that interacts with subsurface resources through a drilled wellbore, designed to obtain, produce, store, or inject materials into or from the earth.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um poço é um sistema projetado que interage com recursos do subsolo através de um furo perfurado, projetado para obter, produzir, armazenar ou injetar materiais na terra ou a partir dela.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every well is an engineered system that bears a subsurface resource interaction function and has a wellbore as component part.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b3448"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2112">
