  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000252">
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every differential pressure switch is a pressure switch that has the function to switch based on differential pressure measurements between two pressure inputs.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(DifferentialPressureSwitch(x) ↔ PressureSwitch(x) ∧ ∃f(DifferentialPressureSwitchingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1003"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A pilot switch intended to switch or give an on/off signal when the measured differential pressure has reached a pre-set value.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DIFFERENTIAL PRESSURE SWITCH&gt; is a &lt;PRESSURE SWITCH&gt; and a &lt;DIFFERENTIAL PRESSURE MEASURING INSTRUMENT&gt;</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um interruptor de pressão diferencial é um interruptor de pressão que possui uma função de comutação de pressão diferencial para comutar ou fornecer sinais liga/desliga quando a pressão diferencial medida entre duas entradas atinge um valor pré-estabelecido.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A differential pressure switch is a pressure switch that bears a differential pressure switching function to switch or provide on/off signals when the measured differential pressure between two inputs reaches a pre-set value.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">differential pressure switch</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">interruptor de pressão diferencial</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000361">
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (ThreePhaseSeparator(x) ↔ (Separator(x) ∧ ∃f (ThreePhaseSeparationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">three phase separator</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">separador trifásico</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;THREE-PHASE SEPARATOR&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;FLUID SEPARATOR&gt; intended to separate three fluids in different phases, typically gas and liquid and water</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A separator intended to separate three fluids in different phases, typically gas and liquid and water</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A vessel that separates the well fluids into gas and two types of liquids: oil and water.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A three-phase separator is a separator that bears a three-phase separation function to separate well fluids into gas, oil, and water phases.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um separador trifásico é um separador que possui uma função de separação trifásica para separar fluidos de poço em fases gasosa, oleosa e aquosa.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b3186"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every three-phase separator is a separator that has the function of separating fluid into gas, oil, and water phases, and has gas outlet, oil outlet, and water outlet as component parts.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/SealingProcess">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1681"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1680"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2879"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2878"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">sealing process</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de vedação</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a valve seat provides a sealing interface for a closure element (gate, ball, disc) to bear against, preventing fluid passage when the valve is closed.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b905">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/DewPointMeasurementProcess"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000214">
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b187"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A depression in the crust of the Earth, caused by plate tectonic activity and subsidence, in which sediments accumulate.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A container intended to store liquid or solid material partly or totally below grade and that is typically open.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A large area with a general containment and an often thick accumulation of rock. A sedimentary basin is an area of regional settling that can be characterized in space, time, and sedimentary fill .It is a physical depression at the earth's surface which accumulates and preserves sediments. The scale of basins varies greatly, from ocean basins to small ponds.                  ==References==                   Helwig, J. A. 1985. Origin and Classification of Sedimentary Basins. Offshore Technology Conference. http://www.doi.org/doi:10.4043/4843-MS</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;BASIN&gt; is a &lt;FLUID CONTAINER&gt;, intended to store liquid or solid material partly or totally below grade and that is typically open</skos:definition>
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000214"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">bacia</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">basin</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">Basin(x) ↔ Vessel(x) ∧ ∃f(StorageFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃p(OpenTop(p) ∧ hasGeometricProperty(x,p)) ∧ ∃q(PartlyBelowGrade(q) ∧ hasInstallationProperty(x,q))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every basin is a vessel that bears a storage function and has an open top configuration and is installed partly below grade.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A basin is a vessel that is designed to store liquid or solid material, characterized by being typically open at the top and installed partly or totally below grade.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma bacia é um vaso projetado para armazenar material líquido ou sólido, caracterizado por ser tipicamente aberto no topo e instalado parcial ou totalmente abaixo do nível do solo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
  </rdf:Description>
