  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000360">
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma Placa que possui geometria de espessura fina e é fabricada através de processos de conformação a frio, tipicamente usada para aplicações de suporte estrutural que requerem peso reduzido ou restrições geométricas específicas.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A Plate that has thin thickness geometry and is manufactured through cold forming processes, typically used for structural support applications requiring reduced weight or specific geometric constraints.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type defined by physical geometry (thinness) and manufacturing method (cold forming). Under OWA, sufficient conditions for thin plates are difficult to specify without risking false positives from specialized hybrid structures that contain thin cold-formed elements but should not be classified as standard thin plates.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">thin plate</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">Placa que possui geometria de espessura fina e</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;THIN PLATE&gt; is a &lt;PLATE&gt; that is a thin steel plate format (Sheet plate) Normally made by coldforming</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">ThinPlate ⊑ Plate ⊓ ∃hasQuality.ThinThickness ⊓ ∃hasQuality.ColdFormedManufacturing</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b3179"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(ThinPlate(x) → Plate(x) ∧ ∃q1(ThinThickness(q1) ∧ hasQuality(x,q1)) ∧ ∃q2(ColdFormedManufacturing(q2) ∧ hasQuality(x,q2)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b764">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/LiquidPortion"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasInput"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000324">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pipe reducer</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">redutor de tubulação</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A pipe reducer is a pipe that has different nominal pipe sizes at its two ends, intended to connect pipes or piping components of different sizes.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um redutor de tubulação é um tubo que possui tamanhos nominais diferentes de tubulação em suas duas extremidades, destinado a conectar tubos ou componentes de tubulação de tamanhos diferentes.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] An 'artefact' that has different nominal pipe size at the two ends, intended to connect pipes or piping components.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] An 'artefact' that has different nominal pipe size at the two ends, intended to connect pipes or piping components.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;PIPE REDUCER&gt; is a &lt;PIPING COMPONENT&gt; and a &lt;REDUCER&gt; either concentric or eccentric of different  nominal pipe size at the two ends, intended to connect pipes or piping components of different nominal pipe sizes or non standard sizes</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2437"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2438"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2440"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2439"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000321"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (PipeReducer(x) → Pipe(x) ∧ ∃i,o (InletEnd(i) ∧ OutletEnd(o) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,i) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,o) ∧ DifferentNominalPipeSizes(i,o)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">As a constructive type defined by geometric configuration, sufficient conditions are omitted under the Open World Assumption to prevent false positives. Complex assemblies or custom manifolds containing size transitions should not be automatically classified as standard pipe reducers without explicit assertion.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every pipe reducer is a pipe that has an inlet end and outlet end with different nominal pipe sizes</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
