  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000365">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A tubing head is a wellhead component that supports the tubing hanger and provides a connection interface for attaching the Christmas tree to the wellhead assembly.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma cabeça de coluna é um componente de cabeça de poço que suporta o suspensor de coluna e fornece uma interface de conexão para fixar a árvore de natal ao conjunto de cabeça de poço.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b3274"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every tubing head is a wellhead component that bears a tubing support and connection function, has a tubing bowl as component part, and has a Christmas tree connection interface as component part.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A flanged spool containing the tubing bowl where the tubing hanger will set and seal.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A wellhead component that supports the tubing hanger and provides a means of attaching the Christmas tree to the wellhead.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;TUBING HEAD&gt; is a &lt;DRILLING COMPONENT&gt; that is fixed to the top of the tubing set in a well.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">cabeça de coluna</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">tubing head</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(TubingHead(x) ↔ WellheadComponent(x) ∧ ∃f(TubingSupportAndConnectionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃p1(TubingBowl(p1) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,p1)) ∧ ∃p2(ChristmasTreeConnectionInterface(p2) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,p2)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b3135">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasInput"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ThermalEnergyPortion"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000311">
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every manifold is an assembly that has-component-part-at-all-times some chamber and has-component-part-at-all-times some multiple fluid openings and bears some fluid distribution function.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">manifold</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">manifold</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Manifold(x) → Assembly(x) ∧ ∃c(Chamber(c) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,c)) ∧ ∃o(MultipleFluidOpenings(o) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,o)) ∧ ∃f(FluidDistributionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um manifold é um conjunto que possui uma câmara com múltiplas aberturas de fluido projetada para distribuir o fluxo de fluido.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A manifold is an assembly that has a chamber with multiple fluid openings designed to distribute fluid flow.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">As a constructive type, manifolds are defined by structural configuration. Under OWA, asserting equivalence would force any assembly with a chamber and multiple openings to be classified as a manifold, potentially misclassifying complex equipment with manifold-like components (e.g., turbine casings, complex valves). Starting with necessary conditions protects against false positives.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2203"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2204"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2205"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] An arrangement of piping or valves designed to control, distribute and typically monitor fluid flow.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A fluid container that contains a chamber with several openings.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that contains a chamber with several openings.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;MANIFOLD&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;FLUID CONDUCTOR&gt; that is an arrangement of piping or valves designed to control, distribute and typically monitor fluid flow</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A junction or center for connecting several pipes and selectively routing the flow.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] IMF purpose entity</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FlowModificationProcess">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1538"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1539"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which the characteristics of fluid flow are altered by a flow modification accessory, resulting in changes to flow patterns, velocity profiles, turbulence levels, or pressure drop characteristics while the fluid passes through or around the device.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de modificação de fluxo</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flow modification process</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
