  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000255">
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1055"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DISTILLATION COLUMN&gt; is  a &lt;DISTILLATION SEPARATOR&gt; and a &lt;PROCESS COLUMN&gt; and a &lt;DISTILLER&gt; intended to enable a distillation process</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A process column intended to enable a distillation process.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A process column intended to enable a distillation process</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (DistillationColumn(x) ↔ (Separator(x) ∧ ∃f (DistillationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">distillation column</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">coluna de destilação</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma coluna de destilação é um separador que possui uma função de destilação para permitir a separação de misturas de fluidos baseada nas diferenças dos pontos de ebulição dos componentes através do equilíbrio vapor-líquido.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A distillation column is a separator that bears a distillation function to enable separation of fluid mixtures based on differences in component boiling points through vapor-liquid equilibrium.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every distillation column is a separator that has the function to perform distillation processes</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
