  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000280">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A flowline is a pipeline that transports oil, gas, or water directly from a wellhead to a manifold or production facility.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma linha de fluxo é um duto que transporta óleo, gás ou água diretamente de uma cabeça de poço para um manifold ou instalação de produção.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b1581"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FLOWLINE&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and  a &lt;PIPELINE&gt; carrying oil, gas or water that connects the wellhead to a manifold or to production facilities, such as heater-treaters and separators</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] The large-diameter metal pipe that connects the bell nipple under the rotary table to the possum belly at the mud tanks.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] The pipe connection between the well and the separators or tank battery.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every flowline is a pipeline that bears a fluid transport function, has a wellhead connection, has a manifold or production facility connection, and transports hydrocarbon fluids.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">linha de fluxo</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flowline</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Flowline(x) ↔ Pipeline(x) ∧ ∃f(FluidTransportFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃w(Wellhead(w) ∧ connectsDirectly(x,w)) ∧ ∃m((Manifold(m) ∨ ProductionFacility(m)) ∧ connectsDirectly(x,m)) ∧ ∃h(HydrocarbonFluid(h) ∧ hasInput(x,h)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b2792">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasInput"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FluidPortion"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b3282">
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b3283"/>
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b3277"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b209">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasInput"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/MechanicalLoad"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000362">
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="ne348407d7b87469ea0df345d3a6b7865b3205"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] An artefact that accepts information in the form of a physical or chemical variable (its input variable) and converts it into an output variable of the same or another nature, according to a definite law.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;TRANSDUCER&gt; is an &lt;ENERGY CONVERTER&gt; that is capable of converting a &lt;PROCESS VARIABLE&gt; in one form or magnitude of energy to another form or magnitude of the same energy</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[isa5_1] a general term for a device, which can be a primary element, transmitter, relay, converter or other device, that receives information in the form of one or more physical quantities, modifies the information or its form, or both if required, and produces a resultant output signal.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Transducer(x) ↔ Instrument(x) ∧ ∃f (TransductionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A transducer is an instrument that bears a TransductionFunction to convert information from one form or magnitude of energy to another form or magnitude.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um transdutor é um instrumento que possui uma FunçãoDeTransdução para converter informação de uma forma ou magnitude de energia para outra forma ou magnitude.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">transdutor</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">transducer</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every transducer is an instrument that has the designed function to convert energy or signal forms while preserving information content.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
